itan Statistical Areas]].\n#The list excludes Canadian cities along the Great Lakes. \n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Combined Statistical Areas, Metropolitan Statistical Areas, and Micropolitan Statistical Areas located on the American side of [[Lake Erie]]\n! Rank\n! Map Reference Number\n! Census Statistical Area\n! 2018 Population\n! Comment\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|15\n|[[Detroit-Warren-Flint, MI CSA|Detroit-Warren-Ann Arbor, MI CSA]]\n|align=right|5,353,002\n|Also located on Lake Huron.\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|12\n|[[Cleveland-Akron-Elyria, OH CSA|Cleveland-Akron-Canton, OH CSA]]\n|align=right|3,599,264\n|\n|-\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|24\n|[[Buffalo-Niagara-Cattaraugus, NY CSA]]\n|align=right|1,206,992\n|Also located on Lake Ontario.\n|-\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|19\n|[[Toledo-Fremont, OH CSA]]\n|align=right|833,576\n| \n|-\n|align=center|5\n|align=center|22\n|[[Erie, PA MSA]]\n|align=right|357,124\n| \n|-\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|23\n|[[Jamestown-Dunkirk-Fredonia, NY \u03bcSA]]\n|align=right|127,939\n| \n|-\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|20\n|[[Sandusky, OH MSA]]\n|align=right|74,615\n| \n|-\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Combined Statistical Areas, Metropolitan Statistical Areas, and Micropolitan Statistical Areas located on the American side of [[Lake Huron]]\n! Rank\n! Map Reference Number\n! Census Statistical Area\n! 2018 Population\n! Comment\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|15\n|[[Detroit-Warren-Flint, MI CSA|Detroit-Warren-Ann Arbor, MI CSA]]\n|align=right|5,353,002\n|Also located on Lake Erie\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|12\n|[[Saginaw-Bay City-Saginaw Township North, MI CSA]]\n|align=right|377,932\n|\n|-\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|4\n|[[Sault Ste. Marie, MI \u03bcSA]]\n|align=right|37,517\n|Also located on Lake Superior\n|-\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|8\n|[[Alpena, MI \u03bcSA]]\n|align=right|28,360\n| \n|-\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Combined Statistical Ar