lude [[Quebec City]], [[Montreal]] and [[Ottawa]] in the Great Lakes Megalopolis, while excluding [[Minneapolis\u2013Saint Paul]], [[Kansas City, Missouri|Kansas City]], [[Cincinnati]], [[Indianapolis]], [[Louisville, Kentucky|Louisville]], and [[Columbus, Ohio|Columbus]].<ref>Example: {{cite map |publisher=The Center for Urban and Regional Studies, [[Youngstown State University]] |title=Great Lakes Megalopolis |url=http://cfweb.cc.ysu.edu/psi/bralich_map/great_lakes_region/great_lakes_megalopolis.pdf |edition= |year=2005 |cartography= |scale= |series= |page= |section= |inset= |accessdate= |isbn= |id= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100705070713/http://cfweb.cc.ysu.edu/psi/bralich_map/great_lakes_region/great_lakes_megalopolis.pdf |archivedate=2010-07-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>  All these partial-consensus and non-consensus cities lie at the eastern, western, and southern fringes of the megalopolis.\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:ISS037-E-8287.jpg|Green Bay (right) to Indianapolis (far lower left)\nFile:ISS053-E-255678.jpg|Lakes Erie (right) and Ontario (left)\nFile:ISS030-E-110240.jpg|Indianapolis (left) to St. Louis (right)\nFile:Saint Paul, Minnesota 9.jpg|Saint Paul\nFile:Appletonskyline.jpg|Fox Cities\nFile:Duluth Skyline.jpg|Duluth\nFile:Cleveland_at_a_glance_by_Lovleet.jpg#/media/File:Cleveland_at_a_glance_by_Lovleet.jpg|Cleveland\nFile:Jackson_Wisconsin_sign_WIS60.jpg|Jackson Wisconsin\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Greatlakes}}\n{{coord|41|N|85|W|region:US_type:adm1st|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Megapolitan areas of the United States]]\n[[Category:Metropolitan areas of Canada]]\n[[Category:Midwestern United States]]\n[[Category:Great Lakes region (U.S.)]]\n[[Category:Geographic regions of Ontario]]\n[[Category:Chicago metropolitan area]]\n[[Category:Regions of Illinois]]\n[[Category:Regions of Ohio]]\n", "name_user": "Genwicky", "label": "safe", "comment": "Edited Minneapolis to Minneapolis/St. Paul to reflect name of metro area and the two principal cities in the region and megalopolis.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Lakes_Megalopolis"}
